caption: Our favorite ramen place in the neighborhood! Please come back. We miss you!
Exceptional and tasty food, I loved the ambience the place has, and the staff members were very nice. Will surely eat here again.
Mmmmmm pretty good portions are kinda small though. They also kinda flood the Takoyaki in Mayo. Overall impressive but not quite S tier.

We recently discovered this place and we absolutely love it. The food is delicious. The staff is super nice. The only drawback for us is that most of the Ramen broth is meat based. But the one vegetable based Ramen really is delicious, and you can add all sorts of toppings. The place is cash only, but they have an ATM on premises.
Best ramen in the area.
Fantastic and delicious food, I loved the character the spot has, and the staff members were friendly. I will surely come back.
One of my go-to places to eat. very good location, always clean, and very good service. I highly recommend them!

Everything was very fresh.  Ramen noodles had nice texture and the broth was delicious. Had the lunch special which comes with a bowl of ramen soup and an appetizer. I had the pork gyoza for appetizer and they were also delicious.  Highly recommended if you like Ramen.
I love the ramen. I hate the pork and chicken.  The pork is always way too fatty and the chicken is hard for some reason.  I order always and it's always the same thing.  U need better protein

Hands down the best Ramen in NYC, and you must order their Spinach / Grapefruit / Avocado salad !!! It is a game changer so salads! The perfect balance of sweet, savory, fresh, and crisp! It pairs perfectly with soup and my favorite thing about this place is if you don’t want beef, they have all chicken ramen! Most ramen joints only serve pork ramen! Not Tenichi! They have so many varieties! Everything is as authentic as it gets! Amazing quality ! My top three go to options are: the chicken ramen, gyoza, and the Spinach / Grapefruit / Avocado salad! You will not be disappointed!
japanese with it's own unique flare. very very tasty. good service. will go again

Beef rayu was definitely good and very tasty. Tan tan , I felt was a tad sweet for some reason, and needed a little more flavor. Pork buns where decent. If am in the area, Wil definitely visit again for the beef rayu.

Loved the service, loved the delicious ramen, and appetizers. They make their own hot oil. I wish I could have their spicy miso ramen every single day! Prices are average for a ramen place. Cash only.
Great food and drinks.  Cash only though so keep that in mind before visiting.
I get to eat here a lot since I work in the area. I love how their service is always great and they keep the spot well kept regularly. Pricing is fair and they serve large portions.
Miss the salmon miso ramen !!

I have been forced into making some very questionable decisions on Ramen due to COVID-19. I really miss this Ramen shop being open I long for the day that the family can come and eat here once again. The service is great my children love the staff. The Ramen oh the Ramen how I miss you.
Friendly servers and delicious food. Will be back soon for sure! It is a cash only place, but there is an ATM inside. P.S your kimchi is amazing🙂
Great place! Thank you Michelle for recommendation 🤗
Great ramen

Best broth. The ten-Ichi pork bone broth is delicious and I recommend it to everyone and so far no one has been disappointed. I recently tried the veggie ramen. It’s a tasty vegan broth. My friend wasn’t as impressed- she prefers a more soy sauce-y flavor. The fried tofu is a treat too. The gyoza is good and crispy. Tip: no you can buy the broth on its own to create your own delicious meals at home- I love that Ten-Ichi Ramen offers this! Very unique. Remember: it’s cash only!
Excellent ramen broth.

Friendly staff and delicious food. Ramen broth is flavorful and ingredients are fresh.

Better than chuko... not a hot take.
they played lana del rey. it was amazing.
Solid, good service, good price, wholesome. Not the best but solid.
Six, seven stars

The miso pork ramen and the beef ramen were absolutely delicious! The broth is super flavorful but not too salty as I find it is in many places, the service was quick and the waiters were really nice. Maybe I just missed something for dessert, but besides that, everything was great and I would totally recommend it.

Came for dinner with a friend and this place hit the spot. It's vegan AND meat friendly which is big cause my friend is a vegetarian and I love me some meat. The restaurant is pretty small but we got seated right away on a Friday night. The broth was real flavorful and the portion sizes are great. I couldn't spot eating it was that good  Ten-Ichi Ramen
Best Ramen in Brooklyn!!!
This is definitely not your college student ramen.  It is very, very good stuff.
I get to eat here a lot since I work close by. I have to say the service is always good and they keep the spot neat regularly. Pricing is convenient and they serve generous portions.
The place offers a fantastic range of delicious food. I love eating here. Employees are always kind, pricing is fair and the place is always clean.

The first time I went to NY was the first time I tried ramen, and it was at Ten-Ichi. It blew my mind, I loved it and ate a  few more times before leaving. The price is ok and the quality is the best. There’re veggie options available

An absolutely amazing ramen experience. I love that the customization of your ramen bowl is made so flexible and easy. I’m a medical user and the experience was ten times advanced. So delicious in every facet and I the Japanese Soda “Ramune” was pretty cool. A must visit here! Larger groups wait longer FYI but nothing drastic
Great service, and the food is so damn good🤗🤗
The noodles were too thin for my taste - didn't really like them

Super friendly and attentive staff. I had the ten-ichi ramen. It was delicious and aromatic. The broth was really rich and had an excellent flavor. Cash only, but ATM on premises. I'll look forward to returning.

Great ramen spot. Cozy and great atmosphere. The food is amazing. We tried 2 ramen and appetizers, it was fresh and delicious. The beer selection is small, it would be great to see more choices. The service was good. If you are looking for good ramen or want to try something new definitely give this place a go.

The food was delicious! The menu was descriptive and the location was very nice. The only down side is that they're cash only. They don't have American soft drinks, like Sprite and Coke and stuff, but they offer really yummy alternatives; Japanese marble soda, very good.
Only ate here once but it was the best tonkatsu broth ever. Very rich and creamy. And I say it as a ramen fanatic. I look forward to going back.

Five stars! Very nice staff, and great food. From the delicious vegan spring rolls, to their pork ramen, creamy, slightly spicy, with a delicious marinated soft boiled egg, and perfectly sautéed pork belly. Washing it down with an ice cold Sapporo on tap 👌
The soup not good they left in the freeze long day more the owner is racist always cry not busy no busy no money
Rammmennnnn! The noodles are homemade,,, it's so good Cute spot, good ramen. It's cozy there
A challenging experience. The noodle were very undercooked, the broth mundane, and the buns were stale.
This place puts lots of love in their ramen. Even for take out the consider the integrity of the food when you ger it home. The flavor on the palate is tantalizing.

Really good food
One of the bestt Ramen spots in Brooklyn.
Great ramen and for a very reasonable price ($13 approx)
Delicious ramen with rich, smoky broth. The buns are amazing too!
Amazing. I really like this place. My go to spot for ramen. I love their Ten-Ichi Ramen. All their appetizers and buns are a must have
Great ramen in a cute place. Many varieties of ramen and at reasonable prices. The poke and wings were good too

It was just okay. The service was very nice and quick and I enjoyed the spring roll appetizer. I didn’t like the veggie ramen though. The broth almost tasted like coconut milk and had a creamy feel. I think a miso broth would have worked much better.

The restaurant is beautiful and has a very comforting feel. A new favourite in the neighborhood The Ten Ichi ramen broth is so flavourful and not overdone. Loved every bit of it.  The Salmon Poke is my favourite. I like pokebowls, but a lot to me have too many flavours that clash, making it oveoverwhelming and hard to finish. Theirs has just enough flavours that compliment each other perfectly. I'm normally not a fan of pickles, but theirs is so sweet and scrumptious, I could eat them anyway.
It was so great, that I couldn't finish it all.
Awesome Ramen.
Love the soup and the ramen.💗
Good fast ramen
Great food, great service.

One of the much better Ramen 🍜 Restaurants in town here. Consistent and flavorful ramen (Ten-ichi ramen dish this time around). Nice texture to the noodles. Delicious duck bun and gyōzas 🥟. Staff is extremely friendly be it to families with children, or if you're someone who strolls in by themselves.  Not the biggest place, but ramen places tend not to be that large anyway. As others mentioned, it's a cash only establishment, but there is an atm inside.
i'm there once a week, and i love it--great comfort food! recommend the rayu beef and ten-ichi ramen; remember it's cash-only
Great food with awesome flavor and reasonable prices, service was great.

They have a kids menu, lunch menu sets and poke bowls there. Ramen is okay. Chicken wings were good. Poke bowl wasn't good at all. I wouldnt recommend the poke bowl but would recommend to try to ramen.
Whack

Not good. Good prices though
Rock shrimp tempura, gyoza, veggie bun, ramen, service, all excellent
Very good ramen and good pricing! My new go to spot for ramen
Delicous ramen, tasty and fresh veggies in it, and great drinks!!!

Good food but overpriced
Pork ramen was very good. I would come back here again.
Great broth! Keep it!

Amazing takoyaki. Very good poke bowls & enjoyable ramen with a rich broth. They have a selection of sake cold or warm, beer (no craft), and wine. No hard liquor. Staff is nice, polite & attentive. Easily visible from the street. No parking lot or structure. No credit or debit cards. There is an ATM inside the restaurant. Wish it wasn’t cash only that’s the only reason they lost a star.
I actually go here for the poke bowls more than anything else.  If you don't know- it's a bowl full of these deliciousness.  Go order one and find out.  Spicy tuna is 👌
Nice decor and pretty decent variety of ramen and other options. Quick service but cash only
The weather was very nice
Great flavor with the pork bone broth as a base
Delicious, wasn't busy mid-afternoon, friendly staff, get the combo special so you can try the snacks
Unfortunately ramen lacked flavor so I doubt I will be back.
Okay bowl of ramen. Wish it wasn't cash only.

Came here with a group of students after graduation rehearsal and wasn't sure what to expect. The place is quaint and very chill. The food was great!!!  Ordered the lunch special - ten ichi ramen and pork bao.  Not bad for $13. The ramen was cooked well and the pork belly was delicious.  Some of the students ordered the duck bao and loved. I'll have to get that next time.  Oh and the place is cash only.

Tasty and satisfying ramen. Not the best in the city but it still hits the spot. Their noodles are the slightly thicker and chewier consistency. I've always experienced pleasant and fast service.  They offer other menu items (gyoza, rice bowl too) but their focus is really on the ramen.

I really like Asian food and it can be hard to find a place that meets my standards, but I love Ten-Ichi! On my last visit I ordered the gyoza. They do an amazing version of homemade gyoza that honestly rivals my own. Their gyoza is impeccably crispy and straight from the frying pan. The meat is quality and the gyoza skin isn't unnecessarily chewy, like some places I've tried. The prices were extremely reasonable, especially for New York. The service took care of me immediately; my server was very attentive and brought my food out quickly. That was a good thing, because I was starving when I visited. The only downside to this place is that it's cash only. As a 21st century Millennial I pretty much never have cash on me, and it's annoying to have to visit the ATM before going to a restaurant.
Amazing Ramen.  Can't wait to go back
A good ramen place.
Great decor, kitchen visible, food is great.

Delicious ramen, totally flavorful, rich and balanced tonkatsu broth. I was not into the flavor of the pork bun sauce but otherwise it was a completely solid pork bun. The staff were super nice, super quick and efficient, and the ambience and decor cozy. I will return for sure.
Food is super good. I love it.
Really really good!!! Delicious
Delicious ramen!
Nice cozy place. They have poke!! Try the Salmon poke! The ramen was okay.
Great ramen and poke.
Decent, but not great ramen. Same for the bun. The Poke, on the other hand, was pretty good. And the service is lovely and the price pretty good.
Omg amazing ramen and even more amazing poké bowls. Do not be deterred by the fact that this place is cash only!
Always great service. Good quality ramen. I would like it if they changed up the menu more often. But it's always a welcome neighborhood treat.
Solid menu, great ramen, excellent service. Great lunch specials.
Ramen was good, but wanted thicker noodles , bone marrow broth was tasty. Service good. Will return.
Very good ramen overall. The sesame, chicken, and veggie ramen is all very good. Would definitely suggest.
I've got the sesame broth ramen 🍜 and spring rolls , it was really great, spicy just the right amount. It was delicious 😋

They should probably save a seat for me since I will be in all winter. I love ramen season. And I love that I have a ramen place close by. I have been stalking this place for the advertised poke (which I haven't tried yet) but I stopped in for the ramen...because cold. I ordered the signature ramen. Just the right amount of pork and flavor. Plus it included the egg. Most places charge extra for that. The ramen hit the spot. I didn't try anything else on this visit but I will definitely be back. Great restaurant to have in the neighborhood. P.S. CASH ONLY (come on brooklyn!)

The ramen was okay. The pork bone broth was nothing special. The short ribs and takoyaki appetizers were really good! The short ribs were tender and the takoyaki was probably the best I've had in NYC compared to the ones in Osaka, Japan. This place is cash only, which kind of sucks since the bill can rack up.

Veggie Ramen was OK, not great. Toppings were lukewarm at best, obviously taken from a fridge) which is fine, just warm them up!). Service was fine but felt a bit rushed, even though the place was pretty empty. Reasonable prices.
I'm a ramen lover...place is great, the veggie ramen is superb! Great lunch option.
Decent ramen for the neighborhood. The soup has improved a lot since they first opened.  Probably as good of a ramen as you're going to get in Park Slope.
Service and food were great. Would go back.
Very solid ramen at good prices in a cute space. Not mind-blowing, but I can't complain.
This place have a good food and friendly server 😊😊
I love this place, awesome food, relaxed environment and nice staff !!
